column5: Hey guys,  Headed out to a small lake outside of cambridge, Friend of mine [Kirk] was always talking about this lake, he likes to tell some tall tales so i didnt belive him until i got there....... one after another it seemed.... enjoy this pics...           Biggest of the day..   Kirk with a few..
Wow...some nice fish there...all from shore I see.  I dont believe you either, can you GPS me those coordinates so I can verify myself?   LOL.  Great job!!!
some decent bass there.. wouldve been better if they were fatter, they need some grub.
Holy jeebus, not bad for close to Cambridge!  .
That first Bass is bizzare looking. The head is twice the size of it's body.  Don't see that too often.
awesome fish and from shore to boot awesome job
Ya a few of them were like that skinny body and huge head... lol
Nice set of bass, looks like some of them could use a few good meals!  I have seen that before (big heads & skinny bodies) on lakes that don't have lots of forage.
Wow nice catch,but yea,they sure are under wieght for thier size.
Those bass are starving to death! No wonder you had such a good morning!  Nice work. I wouldn't count on that pond producing quality bass for too much longer though with bass in that sick of shape.

I just think its hilarious to hear that coming from a Domi fan..... Am I the only one who see's the resemblance between that first bass, and Tie Domi? Don't worry, I am a big Domi fan too, just couldnt resist that one!
Those are indeed some sickly lookin bass, I caught one that looked like those last year in Scugog 21" long and lucky if it weighed 2 Lbs.
